w.unicode.org/wg2/docs/n4964-18060-sinhala-candrabindu.pdf N4964] || {{Citation|title=Proposal to encode the CANDRABINDU for Sinhala|date=2018-02-05|first1=Srinidhi|last1=A|first2=Sridatta|last2=A}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2018/18079-sinhala-candrabindu.pdf L2/18-079]}} || || {{Citation|title=Feedback on Sinhala candrabindu (L2/18-060)|date=2018-03-21|first=Deborah|last=Anderson}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2018/18168-script-rec.pdf L2/18-168]}} || || {{Citation|title=Recommendations to UTC #155 April-May 2018 on Script Proposals|date=2018-04-28|first1=Deborah|last1=Anderson|first2=Ken|last2=Whistler|first3=Roozbeh|last3=Pournader|first4=Lisa|last4=Moore|first5=Hai|last5=Liang|first6=Chris|last6=Chapman|first7=Richard|last7=Cook|section=10. Sinhala}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2018/18115.htm L2/18-115]}} || || {{Citation|title=UTC #155 Minutes|date=2018-05-09|first=Lisa|last=Moore|section=D.4.1}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2018/18183.htm L2/18-183]}} || || {{Citation|title=UTC #156 Minutes|date=2018-11-20|first=Lisa|last=Moore|section=B.1.3.1.1.1}}\n|-\n| || {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/wg2/docs/n5020-M67-Minutes.pdf N5020 (pdf],}} [https://www.unicode.org/wg2/docs/n5020-M67-Minutes.doc doc]) || {{Citation|title=Unconfirmed minutes of WG 2 meeting 67|date=2019-01-11|first=V. S.|last=Umamaheswaran|section=10.3.14}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2020/20052-id-type-changes.txt L2/20-052]}} || || {{Citation|title=Changes to Identifier_Type of some Unicode 13.0 characters|date=2020-01-15|first=Roozbeh|last=Pournader}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2020/20015.htm L2/20-015]}} || || {{Citation|title=Draft Minutes of UTC Meeting 162|date=2020-01-23|first=Lisa|last=Moore|section=B.13.4 Changes to Identifier_Type of some Unicode 13.0 characters}}\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| colspan=\"6\" | {{reflist|group=lower-alpha|refs=<ref name=final>Proposed code points and characters names may differ from final code points and names</ref>}}\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Sinhala Archaic Numbers|Sinhala Archaic Numbers (Unicode block)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Sinhala language}}\n\n[[Category:Unicode blocks]]\n[[Category:Sinhala script]<ref></ref>]<ref>{{\n# \n* [['''''''''']]}}</ref>\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Unicode block\n|blockname  = Sinhala\n|rangestart = 0D80\n|rangeend   = 0DFF\n|script1    = [[Sinhala script|Sinhala]]\n|alphabets  = Sinhala<br />Pali<br />Sanskrit\n|3_0        = 80\n|7_0        = 10\n|13_0 = 1\n|note = <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unicode.org|title=Unicode character database|work=The Unicode Standard|accessdate=2016-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unicode.org/versions/enumeratedversions.html|title=Enumerated Versions of The Unicode Standard|work=The Unicode Standard|accessdate=2016-07-09}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Sinhala''' is a [[Unicode block]] containing characters for the Sinhala and Pali languages of Sri Lanka, and is also used for writing Sanskrit in Sri Lanka. The Sinhala allocation is loosely based on the [[ISCII]] standard, except that Sinhala contains extra [[prenasalized consonant]] letters, leading to inconsistencies with other ISCII-Unicode script allocations.\n\n==Block==\n{{Unicode chart Sinhala}}\n\n==History==\nThe following Unicode-related documents record the purpose and process of defining specific characters in the Sinhala block:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible\"\n|-\n! [[Unicode#Versions|Version]] !! {{nobr|Final code points<ref group=lower-alpha name=final/>}} !! Count !! [[International Committee for Information Technology Standards|L2]]&nbsp;ID !! [[ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 2|WG2]]&nbsp;ID !! Document\n|-\n| rowspan=\"15\" | 3.0 || rowspan=\"15\" width=\"180\" | U+0D82..0D83, 0D85..0D96, 0D9A..0DB1, 0DB3..0DBB, 0DBD, 0DC0..0DC6, 0DCA, 0DCF..0DD4, 0DD6, 0DD8..0DDF, 0DF2..0DF4 || rowspan=\"15\" | 80 || {{nobr|L2/97-019}} || N1480 || {{Citation|title=Request to add Sinhalese to 10646 based on recent Sinhalese Standard (SLS 1134-1996)|date=1996-11-15|first=S. L.|last=Ginige}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|L2/97-019.1}} || || {{Citation|title=Sri Lanka standard Sinhala character code for information interchange}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|L2/97-018}} || [http://www.evertype.com/standards/si/si.html N1473R] || {{Citation|title=Proposal for encoding the Sinhala script in ISO/IEC 10646 (revision 1)|date=1997-03-01|first=Michael|last=Everson|authorlink=Michael Everson}}\n|-\n| || N1532 || {{Citation|title=Comment on Sri Lanka Proposal for Sinhala Script|date=1997-03-07|first=Hugh McGregor|last=Ross|authorlink=Hugh McGregor Ross}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|L2/97-030}} || {{nobr|[http://std.dkuug.dk/jtc1/sc2/wg2/docs/n1503.pdf N1503 (pdf],}} [http://std.dkuug.dk/jtc1/sc2/wg2/docs/n1503.doc doc]) || {{Citation|title=Unconfirmed Minutes of WG 2 Meeting #32, Singapore; 1997-01-20--24|date=1997-04-01|first1=V. S.|last1=Umamaheswaran|first2=Mike|last2=Ksar|section=8.6}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|L2/97-145}} || N1589 || {{Citation|title=Mapping of Sinhala between ISO/IEC 10646 and SLS 1134|date=1997-06-13|first=Michael|last=Everson}}\n|-\n| || N1585 || {{Citation|title=Towards Standard Sinhala Character Code|date=1997-06-25|first=J. B.|last=Disanayaka|authorlink=J. B. Disanayake}}\n|-\n| || N1584 || {{Citation|title=Feedback on Sinhala Script Proposals (N1480, N 1473R, etc.)|date=1997-06-30|first=Glenn|last=Adams}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|L2/97-158}} || N1613 || {{Citation|title=Report of ad-hoc group on Sinhala encoding|date=1997-07-02}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|L2/97-288}} || [http://std.dkuug.dk/jtc1/sc2/wg2/docs/n1603.doc N1603] || {{Citation|title=Unconfirmed Meeting Minutes, WG 2 Meeting # 33, Heraklion, Crete, Greece, 20 June \u2013 4 July 1997|date=1997-10-24|first=V. S.|last=Umamaheswaran|section=8.7}}\n|-\n| {{nobr|[https://www.unicode.org/L2/L1998/02n3190.pdf L2/98-319]}} || [http://std.dkuug.dk/jtc1/sc2/wg2/docs/n1896_02n3190_fpdam21_sinhala.pdf N1896] || {{Citation|title=Revised text of 10646-1/FPDAM 21, AMENDMENT 21: Sinhala