.<ref>Sahn, Michelle. [https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/mycentraljersey/access/1810318691.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=May+19%2C+2004&author=&pub=Home+News+Tribune&desc=Gandhi+rejects+top+post%3B+local+Indians+take+notice+By%3A+MICHELLE+SAHN+STAFF+WRITER&pqatl=google \"Gandhi rejects top post; local Indians take notice\"], ''[[Home News Tribune]]'', May 19, 2004. Accessed March 20, 2012. \"Rohit Vyas, the news director for TV Asia in Edison, hasn't had much sleep lately.... 'We've been covering it extensively,' said the Woodbridge resident.\"</ref>\n* [[Dagmara Wozniak]] (born 1988), [[sabre (fencing)|sabre]] [[fencing|fencer]] named to the U.S. Olympic team at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] and the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in women's sabre.<ref>Chang, Kathy. [https://archive.today/20070623152501/http://ws.gmnews.com/news/2006/0816/Front_page/023.html \"Young fencer enjoys living on the edge: Woodbridge resident hoping for a spot on 2008 Olympic team\"], ''Woodbridge Sentinel'', August 16, 2006. Accessed July 8, 2008. \"Wozniak graduated from Colonia High School in June. She heads to St. John's University in Queens, N.Y., this fall on a full athletic scholarship.\"</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Woodbridge Township, New Jersey}}\n{{Portal|New Jersey}}\n* [http://www.twp.woodbridge.nj.us/ Woodbridge Township website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100316181120/http://woodbridge.injersey.com/ Woodbridge InJersey], community blog\n\n{{Geographic Location\n | Centre    = Woodbridge Township\n | North     = [[Rahway, New Jersey|Rahway]]<br>[[Clark, New Jersey|Clark]]\n | Northeast = [[Linden, New Jersey|Linden]]\n | East      = [[Carteret, New Jersey|Carteret]]<br>[[Staten Island|Staten Island, New York]]\n | Southeast = [[Perth Amboy, New Jersey|Perth Amboy]]\n | South     = [[Sayreville, New Jersey|Sayreville]]\n | Southwest = \n | West      = [[Edison, New Jersey|Edison Township]]\n | Northwest =\n}}\n\n{{Middlesex County, New Jersey}}\n{{New Jersey}}\n\n[[Category:Woodbridge Township, New Jersey| ]]\n[[Category:1669 establishments in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Cannabis in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Faulkner Act (mayor\u2013council)]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1664]]\n[[Category:Townships in Middlesex County, New Jersey]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Township in Middlesex County, New Jersey, United States}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|name                     = Woodbridge Township, New Jersey\n|settlement_type          = [[Township (New Jersey)|Township]]\n|official_name            = Township of Woodbridge\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = Jonathan Dunham House WoodbridgeNJ Built1671.JPG\n|imagesize                = 250x200px\n|image_caption            = [[Jonathan Singletary Dunham House]]\n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               = Woodbridge seal.png\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|image_map                = Woodbridge-twp-nj.PNG\n|mapsize                  = 250x200px\n|map_caption              = Map of Woodbridge Township in Middlesex County. Inset: Location of Middlesex County highlighted in the State of New Jersey.\n|image_map1               = Census_Bureau_map_of_Woodbridge_Township,_New_Jersey.png\n|mapsize1                 = 250x200px\n|map_caption1             = Census Bureau map of Woodbridge Township, New Jersey\n|pushpin_map              = USA New Jersey Middlesex County#USA New Jersey#USA\n|pushpin_label            = Woodbridge\n|pushpin_map_caption      = Location in Middlesex County##Location in New Jersey##Location in the United States\n|pushpin_relief           = yes\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in New Jersey|County]]\n|subdivision_name         = {{US}}\n|subdivision_name1        = {{flag|New Jersey}}\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Middlesex County, New Jersey|Middlesex]]\n\n<!-- Government -->\n|government_type          = [[Faulkner Act (Mayor-Council)]]\n|government_footnotes     = <ref name=DataBook/>\n|governing_body           = Township Council\n|leader_title             = [[Mayor]]\n|leader_name              = [[John McCormac]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]], term ends December 31, 2023)<ref name=Mayor/><ref>[https://www.state.nj.us/dca/home/2020mayors.pdf 2020 New Jersey Mayors Directory], [[New Jersey Department of Community Affairs]]. Accessed February 1, 2020.</ref>\n|leader_title1            = [[City manager|Administrator]]\n|leader_name1             = Vito Cimilluca<ref>[http://www.twp.woodbridge.nj.us/149/Administration-Finance Administration & Finance], Woodbridge Township. Accessed March 9, 2020.</ref>\n|leader_title2            = [[Municipal clerk]]\n|leader_name2             = John M. Mitch<ref>[http://www.twp.woodbridge.nj.us/169/Clerks-Office Clerk's Office], Woodbridge Township. Accessed March 9, 2020.</ref>\n|established_title        = Settled\n|established_date         = 1664\n|established_title2       = Chartered\n|established_date2        = June 1, 1669\n|established_title3       = [[Municipal corporation|Incorporated]]\n|established_date3        = February 21, 1798\n|named_for                = John W. Woodbridge\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|area_footnotes           = <ref name=CensusArea>[http://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/county_sub_list_34.txt 2010 Census Gazetteer Files: New Jersey County Subdivisions], [[United States Census Bureau]]. Accessed May 21, 2015.</ref>\n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_sq_mi         = 24.507\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 23.213\n|area_water_sq_mi         =  1.294\n|area_total_km2           = 63.473\n|area_land_km2            = 60.122\n|area_water_km2           =  3.350\n|area_water_percent       =  5.28\n|area